# On a Windows or Linux PC, install Node v6.11.2 LTS
https://nodejs.org/

# Download the package from GitHub and extract it to a chosen directory, e.g.: C:\Sky-test

# Then open a shell, for instance on Windows:
cmd.exe

# Change path to the chosen directory, for instance on Windows:
cd C:\Sky-test

# Install the necessary packages with the following command
npm install

# then cd into the 'root' directory
cd root

# or
cd C:\Sky-test\root

# start the node server
node --use-strict server.js

# open a browser on the same PC, and point it to the following URLs
# in order to carry out a functional test, or read an error message
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=123101
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=123102
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=123103
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=12310
http://localhost:3000/app/login?custId=123100


### Technical note ###
We're using Node v6.11.2 LTS, the latest LTS version, so we need exactly these versions for the packages below:
"connect": "2.8.0",
"connect-rest": "0.9.14"

even if connect@2.8.0 will result as deprecated during the installation

for reference:
https://www.npmjs.com/package/connect
https://www.npmjs.com/package/connect-rest
